    {
      "title": "Present/Future Tense (المضارع)",
      "titleArabic": "الْفِعْلُ الْمُضَارِع",
      "content": [
        "The present tense (al-muḍāri') expresses ongoing actions or future events. It is formed by adding a prefix to the root and changing the vowel pattern.",
        "The third person masculine singular ('he does') adds يَـ prefix: ذَهَبَ (he went) → يَذْهَبُ (he goes/will go). The final vowel is damma (ُ) in the indicative mood."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Present tense prefix for 'he': يَـ (ya-)",
        "ذَهَبَ → يَذْهَبُ (he goes/will go)",
        "كَتَبَ → يَكْتُبُ (he writes/will write)",
        "The muḍāri' can mean present or future depending on context"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "يَذْهَبُ", "english": "he goes / he will go" },
        { "arabic": "يَكْتُبُ", "english": "he writes / he will write" },
        { "arabic": "يَقْرَأُ", "english": "he reads / he will read" },
        { "arabic": "يَذْهَبُ الطَّالِبُ إِلَى الْمَدْرَسَةِ", "english": "The student goes to the school" }
      ]
    }
  ],
